g.title: root
g.text: CHEMICAL REACTIONS

g.title: subtopic_0
g.text: INTRODUCTION TO CHEMICAL REACTIONS

g.title: subtopic_0_point_0
g.text: Chemical reactions involve the rearrangement of atoms.

g.title: subtopic_0_point_1
g.text: Reactants are the starting materials, and products are the resulting substances.

g.title: subtopic_0_point_2
g.text: Reactions are accompanied by energy changes (exothermic or endothermic).

g.title: subtopic_0_point_3
g.text: Chemical equations represent reactions symbolically.

g.title: subtopic_1
g.text: TYPES OF CHEMICAL REACTIONS

g.title: subtopic_1_point_0
g.text: Synthesis reactions: Combining simpler substances to form a more complex one.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_1
g.text: Decomposition reactions: Breaking down a complex substance into simpler ones.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_2
g.text: Single displacement reactions: One element replacing another in a compound.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_3
g.text: Double displacement reactions: Anions and cations of two compounds switch places.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_4
g.text: Redox reactions: Involve oxidation (loss of electrons) and reduction (gain of electrons).

g.title: subtopic_1_point_5
g.text: Combustion reactions: Rapid reactions with oxygen, often producing heat and light.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_6
g.text: Acid-base reactions: Transfer of protons (H+) between species.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_7
g.text: Precipitation reactions: Formation of a solid from a solution.

g.title: subtopic_1_point_8
g.text: Complexation reactions: Formation of coordination complexes between ligands and metal atoms.

g.title: subtopic_2
g.text: CHEMICAL KINETICS AND EQUILIBRIUM

g.title: subtopic_2_point_0
g.text: Reaction rate: Speed at which a reaction proceeds.

g.title: subtopic_2_point_1
g.text: Factors affecting reaction rate: Concentration, temperature, surface area, catalysts, activation energy.

g.title: subtopic_2_point_2
g.text: Chemical equilibrium: State where forward and reverse reaction rates are equal.

g.title: subtopic_2_point_3
g.text: Le Chatelier's principle: Predicting the effect of changes on equilibrium.

g.title: subtopic_2_point_4
g.text: Equilibrium constant: Quantifies the relative amounts of reactants and products at equilibrium.

g.title: subtopic_3
g.text: CHEMICAL THERMODYNAMICS

g.title: subtopic_3_point_0
g.text: Enthalpy (ΔH): Heat change during a reaction.

g.title: subtopic_3_point_1
g.text: Entropy (ΔS): Change in disorder during a reaction.

g.title: subtopic_3_point_2
g.text: Gibbs free energy (ΔG): Determines the spontaneity of a reaction.

g.title: subtopic_3_point_3
g.text: Relationship between ΔG, ΔH, and ΔS: ΔG = ΔH - TΔS.

g.title: subtopic_3_point_4
g.text: Exothermic reactions (ΔH < 0): Release heat.

g.title: subtopic_3_point_5
g.text: Endothermic reactions (ΔH > 0): Absorb heat.

g.title: subtopic_4
g.text: REACTION MECHANISMS AND ELEMENTARY REACTIONS

g.title: subtopic_4_point_0
g.text: Elementary reactions: Single-step reactions.

g.title: subtopic_4_point_1
g.text: Reaction mechanisms: Sequence of elementary reactions.

g.title: subtopic_4_point_2
g.text: Unimolecular reactions: Involve a single molecule.

g.title: subtopic_4_point_3
g.text: Bimolecular reactions: Involve two molecules.

g.title: subtopic_4_point_4
g.text: Transition state theory: Explains reaction rates based on the energy of the transition state.

g.title: subtopic_5
g.text: ORGANIC REACTION MECHANISMS

g.title: subtopic_5_point_0
g.text: Substitution reactions: Replacement of a functional group.

g.title: subtopic_5_point_1
g.text: Addition reactions: Adding atoms or groups to a multiple bond.

g.title: subtopic_5_point_2
g.text: Elimination reactions: Removing atoms or groups to form a multiple bond.

g.title: subtopic_5_point_3
g.text: Nucleophilic and electrophilic reactions.

g.title: subtopic_5_point_4
g.text: Radical reactions: Involve free radicals.

g.title: subtopic_6
g.text: CATALYSIS

g.title: subtopic_6_point_0
g.text: Catalysts: Substances that increase reaction rates without being consumed.

g.title: subtopic_6_point_1
g.text: Homogeneous and heterogeneous catalysis.

g.title: subtopic_6_point_2
g.text: Enzyme catalysis: Biological catalysts.

g.title: subtopic_7
g.text: APPLICATIONS OF CHEMICAL REACTIONS

g.title: subtopic_7_point_0
g.text: Chemical synthesis: Production of new compounds.

g.title: subtopic_7_point_1
g.text: Industrial processes: Manufacturing of various materials.

g.title: subtopic_7_point_2
g.text: Biochemical reactions: Metabolic processes in living organisms.
